<% content_for(:title) { "About — Save Utah" } %>

<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-utah-navy">About Save Utah</h1>

  <div class="mt-8 prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700">
    <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed">
      <strong class="text-utah-navy">Save Utah</strong> is a nonpartisan civic engagement platform
      dedicated to government transparency and citizen empowerment. We believe that an informed public
      is the foundation of a healthy democracy.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-utah-navy mt-10">Our Mission</h2>
    <p>
      We track Utah's elected officials at both the state and federal level — their voting records,
      their positions, and how they represent the people of Utah. Our goal is to make this information
      accessible, understandable, and actionable.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-utah-navy mt-10">What We Do</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 mt-4">
      <li class="flex items-start">
        <span class="text-utah-red font-bold mr-3 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
        <span><strong>Track Voting Records</strong> — See how every Utah representative votes on bills that matter to you.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start">
        <span class="text-utah-red font-bold mr-3 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
        <span><strong>Plain Language Summaries</strong> — We explain what bills actually mean, beyond the legal jargon.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start">
        <span class="text-utah-red font-bold mr-3 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
        <span><strong>Action Scripts</strong> — Ready-made call scripts and email templates so you can contact your officials in minutes.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start">
        <span class="text-utah-red font-bold mr-3 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
        <span><strong>Open Data</strong> — All our data comes from public government APIs and records.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-utah-navy mt-10">Data Sources</h2>
    <p>We pull data from official government sources to ensure accuracy:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 mt-4">
      <li><strong>Congress.gov API</strong> — Federal member data, bills, and House/Senate votes</li>
      <li><strong>Utah Legislature API</strong> — State legislators, state bills, and floor votes</li>
      <li><strong>OpenStates</strong> — Supplementary state-level data</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-4">
      Data is refreshed regularly. If you notice any inaccuracies, please let us know.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-utah-navy mt-10">Nonpartisan Commitment</h2>
    <p>
      Save Utah is not affiliated with any political party, candidate, or government entity.
      We present factual voting records and let you draw your own conclusions.
      Democracy works best when citizens have access to accurate information.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
